race.comment: Siding with the newcomer SNOBBERY (7), a gelding by Savabeel on debut for the Busuttin & Young stable. He's been jumping out fairly well leading into this for strong connections and the 1600m should be right up his alley. Doubt he needs to be s star to be going close. PRINCE OF POETRY (6) improved second up going to 1400m at Sale and should be fitter again now. This suits. POSITIVO (4) was another that improved getting up in trip last start at Werribee having ran on strongly into second over 1429m. Now to 1600m, he can go again and take beating. SUNSHINE STAR (11) was just fair on debut at Pakenham but should find this an easier maiden and can improve quickly. DETROIT DREAMING (10) wasn't far away at Wodonga last time and has minor claims.
